article.headline: Lehigh beats Loyola (Md.) 66-52
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Jesse Chuku had 15 points and Mackey McKnight had seven points, 10 rebounds and six assists on Saturday to lead Lehigh over Loyola (Md.) 66-52. Lehigh jumped ahead 15-6, led the entire game and used two second-half runs to pull ahead by a comfortable margin. After Loyola fell behind early, it closed to within one score on four different occasions, the last coming on a 29-27 deficit early in the second half. Lehigh answered with a 10-2 run to take a 39-29 lead on Stefan Cvrkalj's 3-pointer at the 13:27 mark, and then a 9-2 run to go ahead 51-38 with 7:42 left. Lehigh led by no less than nine points from there. Tim Kempton added 14 points for Lehigh (13-12, 6-6 Patriot League) which made 26 of 30 free throws and outrebounded Loyola 45-30. Eric Laster had 17 points and Jordan Latham added 13 points for Loyola (10-13, 5-7).
